From: Vinayak Kale <vinayak.kale@seagate.com>
Date: Tue, 27 Oct 2015 13:11:46 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 364/827] libata: enable LBA flag in taskfile for ata_scsi_pass_thru()

This patch comes from:
  https://github.com/Xilinx/linux-xlnx.git

Enable LBA in taskfile flags for ata_scsi_pass_thru()

Signed-off-by: Vinayak Kale <vinayak.kale@seagate.com>
Signed-off-by: Tejun Heo <tj@kernel.org>
(cherry picked from commit 5f8e7f17f6f5472d8029c22b1b8d3f9a4b1c8dff)
Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/ata/libata-scsi.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/ata/libata-scsi.c b/drivers/ata/libata-scsi.c
index 6b7ce84..9f38469 100644
--- a/drivers/ata/libata-scsi.c
+++ b/drivers/ata/libata-scsi.c
@@ -2943,6 +2943,9 @@ static unsigned int ata_scsi_pass_thru(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc)
 	if ((tf->protocol = ata_scsi_map_proto(cdb[1])) == ATA_PROT_UNKNOWN)
 		goto invalid_fld;
 
+	/* enable LBA */
+	tf->flags |= ATA_TFLAG_LBA;
+
 	/*
 	 * 12 and 16 byte CDBs use different offsets to
 	 * provide the various register values.
